The paper deals with streaming high-quality 3D graphics, which is a topic that falls under computer graphics (cs.GR). The use of point clouds and the need for efficient streaming also suggests a connection to multimedia (cs.MM) and networking (cs.NI). The paper also mentions the use of thinning approaches and semantic linking to human visual acuity, which are techniques commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the design of a DASH Media Presentation Description manifest speci.c for point cloud streaming suggests a connection to distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
